article.headline: DePaul 72, Tulane 58
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. (AP) -- Andre Brown tied a career-high with 24 points and had 12 rebounds as DePaul defeated Tulane 72-58 Tuesday night. DePaul (12-7, 5-3 Conference USA) pulled away early in the second half. Brown, playing in his second game back after missing nine straight with a knee injury, sparked a 9-2 DePaul run in the second half, by scoring all nine points by himself. He had a breakaway dunk to give DePaul a 51-34 lead with 14:03 left. Drake Diener added 18 points for DePaul, while Delonte Holland scored 11 points and Quemont Greer had 11 points and 12 rebounds. The Blue Demons have won five of their last six games. Tulane (7-12, 0-8 USA) was led by Quincy Davis with 19 points and eight rebounds. DePaul opened the game with a 17-4 lead. Diener scored seven points in the span and Brown capped it off with an alley-oop dunk from Sammy Mejia. Tulane closed the gap in the first half by outscoring DePaul 12-1 in a 3:25 period. Vytas Tatarunas had a basket to cut the DePaul lead to 18-16 with 11:25 left. DePaul led 37-29 at half. Brown scored 12 first-half points for DePaul and Diener added nine. Ben Benfield scored nine points for Tulane. DePaul outrebounded Tulane in the game 50-38.
